title.narrative: WASH - COMMUNITY ENVIRONMENT HIGIENIC AND SAFE

description.narrative: Strengthened national capacities for implementing sustainable and equitable Water, Sanitation, and Hygiene (WASH) programming at scale, which contributes to Safe And Equitable Water, Sanitation And Hygiene Services And Practices, Safe And Equitable Water, Sanitation And Hygiene Services And Practices (Covid), Water, Sanitation And Hygiene Systems And Empowerment Of Communities, Water, Sanitation And Hygiene Systems And Empowerment Of Communities (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2021, pregnant women and new-borns, children and adolescents have equitable access to essential lifesaving health care services

title.narrative: Strengthened national capacities for implementing sustainable and equitable WASH programming at scale

description.narrative: UNICEF response was scaled up as an essential component to support COVID-19 prevention, and health, education, nutrition and protection outcomes. UNICEF reached more than 2,300,000 people with access to safe water, 80% of these through resilient approaches, such as rehabilitation of water supply systems.Lifesaving hand-hygiene was also supported for more than 600,000 people, through information and distribution of essential hygiene products in community, health facilities and shelter contexts, created for COVID19 quarantine. UNICEF also reached 94 schools and 194 health care facilities, to support COVID19 prevention and care, with WASH infrastructure, supplies and technical assistance under an IPC;strategy. | Status:Met | As-of Date:18/01/2021
